l morphemes, into grammatical sentences, and morphosyntax as being an umbrella term for all morphological relations between these linguistic units, which either trigger morphological marking (e.g. explicit case morphemes) or are related to ordering issues (e.g. subjects precede finite verbs whenever there is number agreement between them). All 24 chapters adopt a comparative perspective on these two fields of research, highlighting cross-linguistic grammatical similarities and differences within the Romance language family. In addition, many chapters address issues related to variation observable within individual Romance languages, and grammatical change from Latin to Romance.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Aug 2020) 0aRomance languagesxMorphosyntax. 0aRomance languagesxSyntax. 4aMorphosyntax. 4aRomance Languages. 4aRomance Linguistics. 4aRomanische Sprachen. 4aSyntax. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Syntax.2bisacsh1 aDufter, Andreas, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aStark, Elisabeth, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2017z9783110547887oZDB-23-DSP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManuals of Romance Linguistics Packagez97831106438240 cEPUBz97831103934220 cprintz978311037693740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311037708840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110377088423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110377088.jpg  a978-3-11-062526-4  EBOO